' @id(USE-DEPLOY-PURPOSE) <<added>> this cycle (0016)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-ACCESS-CHECK) <<added>> this cycle (0016)
' Cycle 0016 diff (current side): /mdd-deploy gains two adaptive gates —
' deployment-purpose confirmation and an access-completeness pass —
' joining the existing dialect gate. Nothing removed; Guide / Dialect /
' Inspect are reused unchanged.
title /mdd-deploy adaptive gates · cycle 0016 diff (current)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform)" as Dialect
  usecase "Confirm the deployment PURPOSE\n(dev/staging/prod) before any\npurpose-driven default" as Purpose <<added>>
  usecase "Account for who READS and WRITES\nevery secured store (identity +\nadmitted path) before emitting" as AccessCheck <<added>>
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Purpose
Op --> AccessCheck
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Purpose : <<include>>
Guide ..> AccessCheck : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>
@enduml
